; smulo on bitvec 1
; In 1-bit signed: value 1 represents -1.
; smulo(1, 1): signed multiplication (-1) * (-1) = +1, which overflows
; 1-bit signed (range is {-1, 0}). So smulo should be true.
1 sort bitvec 1
2 one 1
; smulo(1, 1) on 1-bit: (-1) * (-1) = +1 overflows -> true
3 smulo 1 2 2
4 not 1 3
5 bad 4
